13.5 AREAS
The Area Problem ! Definition of Area
We have seen that limits are needed to compute the slope of a tangent line or an instanta-
neous rate of change. Here we will see that they are also needed to find the area of a re-
gion with a curved boundary. The problem of finding such areas has consequences far be-
yond simply finding area. (See Focus on Modeling, page 884.)
! The Area Problem
One of the central problems in 
y $ f 1cax 2lculus is the area problem: Find the area of the region Sthat lies under the curve from a to b. This means that S, illustrated in Figure 1,
is bounded by the graph of a function f (where f 1x 2 ' 0), the vertical lines x $ a and 
x $ b, and the x-axis.
