In trying to solve the area problem, we have to ask ourselves: What is the meaning of
the word area? This question is easy to answer for regions with straight sides. For a rec-
tangle, the area is defined as the product of the length and the width. The area of a trian-
gle is half the base times the height. The area of a polygon is found by dividing it into tri-
angles (as in Figure 2) and adding the areas of the triangles.
